  # Claude vs. ChatGPT: What's the difference?
  
  By Ryan Kane · May 27, 2025
  
  [Share article on X](https://x.com/intent/post?url=https://zapier.com/blog/claude-vs-chatgpt/ "Share article on X")[Share article on LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite?url=https://zapier.com/blog/claude-vs-chatgpt/ "Share article on LinkedIn")[Share article on Reddit](https://www.reddit.com/submit?url=https://zapier.com/blog/claude-vs-chatgpt/ "Share article on Reddit")
  
  ![Hero image with the Claude and ChatGPT logos](https://images.ctfassets.net/lzny33ho1g45/4vz596IkendsVTaLDpQ3c/cedabeafc83c15234fa12f34abf67419/claude-vs-chatgpt.jpg?fm=jpg&q=31&fit=thumb&w=1520&h=760)
  
  When OpenAI launched ChatGPT in late 2022, tech writers (myself included) became obsessed with testing its limits. Could it write poetry? Debug code? Explain quantum physics to a five-year-old? Once Anthropic's Claude entered the scene a few months later, the focus shifted to head-to-head task comparisons (like counting objects or navigating ethical dilemmas) to try to figure out which model was more capable.
  
  Now—after countless model updates, and with potentially game-changing AI agent capabilities on the horizon—assessing object-counting accuracy feels less relevant. With a few exceptions, Anthropic and OpenAI's flagship models are essentially at parity. That means to usefully compare them, we need to focus less on under-the-hood power and more on the features and specialized use cases that make each app unique.
  
  In this article, I'll help you understand what sets Claude and ChatGPT apart—focusing on the latest models like Claude Sonnet 4 and ChatGPT's GPT-4o and o1—so you can choose the tool that best fits your workflow.
  
  **Table of contents:**
  
  - [Claude vs. ChatGPT at a glance](https://zapier.com/blog/claude-vs-chatgpt/#glance)
  
  - [Both apps are ridiculously easy to use and offer state-of-the-art models](https://zapier.com/blog/claude-vs-chatgpt/#models)
  
  - [Claude is a better partner for creative work](https://zapier.com/blog/claude-vs-chatgpt/#creative)
  
  - [ChatGPT can be used to generate images (and videos, via Sora)](https://zapier.com/blog/claude-vs-chatgpt/#images)
  
  - [Claude is a more helpful coding assistant](https://zapier.com/blog/claude-vs-chatgpt/#coding)
  
  - [ChatGPT lets you build your own chatbot](https://zapier.com/blog/claude-vs-chatgpt/#build)
  
